description.narrative: GCO remains committed to supporting the integrated management of acute malnutrition (IMAM) program of the Ministry of Health. This entails procuring lifesaving nutrition supplies for the prevention and treatment of severe malnutrition among children under five years of age. This lifesaving intervention provided cure for many children admitted into the treatment programm. GCO technical staff ensured this intervention was integrated with other child survival activities. The agency supported the institutional strengthening of optimal infant and young child feeding (IYCF) for protection and promotion of breastfeeding. This was integrated with other child survival initiatives. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:29/12/2021
